timeline.message:
More strict decoding of HTTP/1.x start-line

Motivation:

RFC7230 allows only a single SP between start-line components:
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230#section-3.1
And it adds additional restrictions for which characters are
allowed for each individual component.

Modifications:

- Skip only limited number of prefacing control characters;
- Do not allow leading/trailing WS for start-line;
- Expect only a single SP/HTAB as a delimiter between start-line
components;
- Verify that request-target and reason-phrase has only allowed
characters;
- Allow only upper-case letters for HTTP-method;
- Simplify header field-name/field-value parsing;
- Improved parsing for HTTP version;
- Share common code between `HttpRequestDecoderTest` and
`HttpResponseDecoderTest`;
- Address issues with existing tests and add more tests
for decoders;

Result:

More strict decoding of HTTP/1.x start-line.

